Create an EC2 key pair in AWS
Start here
Generate the key pair in the EC2 console so AWS stores the public key and you keep the private key.

Sign in to the AWS Console

Go to EC2 → Network & Security → Key Pairs

Click Create key pair

Enter a name (e.g., soc-ec2-key)

Key pair type: RSA

Private key file format: pem

Click Create key pair and save the downloaded .pem file somewhere safe (e.g., C:\Users\YourUser\keys\soc-ec2-key.pem)
